results.name: A277893(n) = the least k > n for which A277892(k) = A277892(n), 0 if no such number exists.
comment: a(n) is the least k larger than n for which the number of divisors of A048675(k) is equal to the number of divisors of A048675(n) (counted with multiplicity), and 0 if no such number exists (which happens only for n=2).
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..102 (computed from the b-file provided by Hans Havermann for A277892)
program: (Scheme) (define (A277893 n) (cond ((= 2 n) 0) (else (let ((v (A277892 n))) (let loop ((k (+ 1 n))) (if (= (A277892 k) v) k (loop (+ 1 k))))))))
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Nov 08 2016
